ose all of their points, are knocked out and may no longer participate in the tournament.</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">4. If a player loses all of his/her points, the remaining games of the round are not played.</span></p>\r\n', 0),
(8, 'Yatzy tournament', '<p>\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">5. If, after the stakes for the game have already been made, one player does not finish the game, irrespective of whether this is voluntary, due to a loss of connection or for any other technical problem, the &lsquo;ghost rule&rsquo; comes into force, whereby the computer takes the place of the departed player. If the computer wins, the game is not rated. A loss for the computer, however, is rated. Even if a player returns to the match, he/she cannot win, but may prevent the loss.&nbsp;</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">6. The risk of technical problems arising during a game, which may lead to a player conceding involuntarily, is understood and accepted by all players. GameTwist.de accepts no responsibility for the completion of every game on every computer.</span></p>\r\n', 8, '2013-01-24 00:00:00', '2013-01-26 00:00:00', '<p>\r\n	<span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">5. If, after the stakes for the game have already been made, one player does not finish the game, irrespective of whether this is voluntary, due to a loss of connection or for any other technical problem, the &lsquo;ghost rule&rsquo; comes into force, whereby the computer takes the place of the departed player. If the computer wins, the game is not rated. A loss for the computer, however, is rated. Even if a player returns to the match, he/she cannot win, but may prevent the loss.&nbsp;</span><br style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" />\r\n	<span style="